# No `*` in function headers

Avoid using `*` (keyword-only separator) in Python function signatures. It makes quick copy/paste of functions into notebooks/scripts annoying (positional args wonâ€™t work unless you also copy callsites).

## Prefer

```python
def my_func(a, b, force_reload=False, dosave=True, save_dir=None, foo_kwargs=None):
    foo_kwargs_ = {'force_reload': False, 'dosave': True}
    if foo_kwargs is not None:
        foo_kwargs_.update(dict(foo_kwargs))
    # ...
```

## Avoid

```python
def my_func(a, b, *, force_reload=False, dosave=True, save_dir=None, foo_kwargs=None):
    ...
```

